---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { BOOK_TITLE, BOOK_SUBTITLE, AUTHOR, AMAZON_URL } from '../consts.js';
---

<BaseLayout
  title={null}
  description={`${BOOK_TITLE}: ${BOOK_SUBTITLE}. By ${AUTHOR}.`}
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="bg-cream">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-16 md:py-24 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 md:gap-16 items-start">
      <!-- Book cover -->
      <div class="order-2 md:order-1">
        <img
          src="/book-cover.jpg"
          alt={`Cover of ${BOOK_TITLE} by ${AUTHOR}`}
          width="800"
          height="1200"
          class="aspect-[2/3] w-full max-w-sm mx-auto rounded-md shadow-2xl object-cover"
        />
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-sm mx-auto text-center text-sm text-ink/80">
          Don't you just love this book cover? It was created by the incredibly talented
          <strong class="text-navy">McKay Fife</strong>. The rest of his work is just as good.
          <a
            href="https://www.instagram.com/mckayfife_illustration/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-navy underline hover:text-gold font-medium"
          >Go see for yourself</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Headline + email form -->
      <div class="order-1 md:order-2">
        <p class="text-gold uppercase tracking-widest text-sm font-semibold mb-4">A new book by {AUTHOR}</p>
        <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl leading-tight text-navy mb-4">
          From Reluctant Missionary to Devoted Disciple
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-ink/80 mb-8">
          Lessons of faith, focus, and the Savior's love, drawn from one missionary's journey,
          and an invitation to walk with Him in your own.
        </p>

        <!-- Launch banner -->
        <a
          href={AMAZON_URL}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="block bg-navy rounded-lg px-5 py-4 mb-6 no-underline hover:bg-navy/90 transition-colors text-center"
        >
          <p class="font-heading text-xl md:text-2xl text-gold m-0 leading-tight">
            Now available on Amazon: order your copy today.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-white/90 mt-1 m-0">
            Paperback also available June 1st.
          </p>
        </a>

        <!-- Free guide intro -->
        <h2 class="font-heading text-2xl md:text-3xl text-navy mb-3 leading-tight">
          Built for the Journey
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-ink/80 mb-3">
          This is more than a newsletter. When you join, you get the Five Lessons Guide
          today and everything I create going forward. Practical resources built for:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-base md:text-lg text-ink/80 mb-3 space-y-1">
          <li>Those still deciding if they want to serve</li>
          <li>Those currently serving</li>
          <li>Those just returned home</li>
          <li>The parents that pray for them</li>
          <li>Leaders walking alongside them</li>
          <li>Anyone still learning to walk with Him</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-ink/80 mb-5">Free. Always yours.</p>

        <!-- Kit (ConvertKit) email form -->
        <script async data-uid="a444096c4c" src="https://learning-to-walk-with-him.kit.com/a444096c4c/index.js"></script>
        <p class="mt-3 text-base md:text-lg text-center" style="color: #2c2c2c;">
          I'll also send you occasional letters. Unsubscribe anytime.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FROM THE BOOK -->
  <section class="bg-navy text-cream">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-12 grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-3">
      <figure class="text-center md:text-left">
        <blockquote class="font-heading text-xl italic leading-snug">
          "God doesn't waste anyone's willingness to try."
        </blockquote>
        <figcaption class="mt-2 text-sm text-cream/70"><em>Learning to Walk with Him</em></figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="text-center md:text-left">
        <blockquote class="font-heading text-xl italic leading-snug">
          "The Lord measures your offering, not your timeline."
        </blockquote>
        <figcaption class="mt-2 text-sm text-cream/70"><em>Learning to Walk with Him</em></figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="text-center md:text-left">
        <blockquote class="font-heading text-xl italic leading-snug">
          "If He can work with me, He can work with you."
        </blockquote>
        <figcaption class="mt-2 text-sm text-cream/70"><em>Learning to Walk with Him</em></figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT THE BOOK IS -->
  <section class="bg-cream">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 md:py-20">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl text-navy mb-6">What the book is</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-ink/85 mb-4">
        <em>Learning to Walk with Him</em> is part memoir, part field guide for discipleship.
        It tells the story of a reluctant young missionary who discovered, slowly and through
        many missteps, that following the Savior is not about perfect performance. It is
        about a deepening walk.
      </p>
      <p class="text-lg text-ink/85">
        Through five lessons drawn from the mission field, Ken offers practical,
        scripturally-rooted invitations to walk a little closer to Christ each day.
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-6 space-y-2 text-lg text-ink/85 list-none p-0">
        <li><strong class="text-navy">Lesson 1.</strong> You never know who you will touch.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-navy">Lesson 2.</strong> You are sent where you are sent for a reason.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-navy">Lesson 3.</strong> Keep the Savior's life and ministry as the focus in all you do.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-navy">Lesson 4.</strong> Don't underestimate the power of prayer and the Lord's love for you.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-navy">Lesson 5.</strong> Baptisms aren't the focus; the Savior's love is.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
  <section class="bg-white border-y border-navy/10">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 md:py-20">
      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl text-navy mb-8">Who it's for</h2>
      <ul class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 list-none p-0">
        <li class="border-l-4 border-gold pl-4">
          <p class="font-heading text-xl text-navy mb-1">Returned and current missionaries</p>
          <p class="text-ink/80">Anyone who has ever felt unworthy of the calling, and is ready to keep walking anyway.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="border-l-4 border-gold pl-4">
          <p class="font-heading text-xl text-navy mb-1">Parents and youth leaders</p>
          <p class="text-ink/80">Looking for honest stories that frame faith as a relationship, not a performance.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="border-l-4 border-gold pl-4">
          <p class="font-heading text-xl text-navy mb-1">Disciples in any season</p>
          <p class="text-ink/80">Whether you're stepping back, starting over, or steady, these lessons meet you where you are.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="border-l-4 border-gold pl-4">
          <p class="font-heading text-xl text-navy mb-1">Skeptics willing to read with an open heart</p>
          <p class="text-ink/80">No shame, no pressure. Just an invitation to walk and see.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- AUTHOR BIO -->
  <section class="bg-cream">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 py-16 md:py-20 grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr] gap-10 items-start">
      <div>
        <img
          src="/img_1996.PNG"
          alt={`Photo of ${AUTHOR}`}
          width="400"
          height="400"
          class="aspect-square w-48 rounded-full object-cover border-4 border-green/30 mx-auto md:mx-0"
        />
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl text-navy mb-4">About {AUTHOR}</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-ink/85 mb-4">
          Ken Smith didn't leave on his mission with a burning testimony. He went because he
          didn't want to break his mother's heart, and because all his friends were going.
          From 1991 to 1993 he served in the Japan Fukuoka Mission, where the love of
          President and Sister Figuerres and the patient teaching of the Savior began to
          reshape a reluctant young missionary into a disciple.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-ink/85 mb-6">
          In the years since, Ken has invested deeply in the faith of young people, serving
          as a bishop, as a counselor in his stake presidency, and now on a Young Single
          Adult stake high council alongside his wife. He and his wife live in the Pacific
          Northwest, where Ken also holds a senior leadership role in technology. Above all
          else, he is a husband, father, and grandfather. <em>Learning to Walk with Him</em>
          is his first book.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/about"
          class="inline-block rounded-md border border-navy text-navy px-5 py-2 font-medium hover:bg-navy hover:text-cream no-underline"
        >
          Read more about Ken
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
